Title: Trump-backed Michigan secretary of state nominee said abortion is \'91child sacrifice\'92\
Author: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnn.com/profiles/em-steck"}}{\fldrslt Em Steck}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnn.com/profiles/andrew-kaczynski"}}{\fldrslt Andrew Kaczynski}}\
Publication_Date: Updated 12:23 PM EDT, Mon July 4, 2022\
Article_Content: CNN \'a0\'97\'a0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Before becoming the Trump-backed Republican nominee for Michigan secretary of state, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnn.com/2021/11/16/politics/kristina-karamo-michigan-secretary-of-state-candidate/index.html"}}{\fldrslt Kristina Karamo}} said that abortion is \'93child sacrifice\'94 and a \'93satanic practice.\'94 \'93Abortion is really nothing new. The child sacrifice is a very satanic practice, and that\'92s precisely what abortion is. And we need to see it as such,\'94 Karamo, a community college professor, said in an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/life-is-so-beautiful/id1526611407?i=1000494511417"}}{\fldrslt October 2020 episode of her podcast \'93It\'92s Solid Food,\'94}} which CNN\'92s KFile reviewed. \'93When people in other cultures, when they engage in child sacrifice, they didn\'92t just sacrifice the child for the sake of bloodshed,\'94 Karamo said later in the episode. \'93They sacrificed the child cuz they were hoping to get prosperity and that\'92s precisely why people have abortion now. \'91Because I\'92m not ready. I don\'92t wanna have a baby. I don\'92t feel like it. I don\'92t have time. I wanna make more money. I want my freedom.\'92 So you\'92re sacrificing that child hoping to get something out of their death, which is your freedom, your happiness, your prosperity.\'94 In another comment, Karamo called abortion the \'93the greatest crime of our nation\'92s history.\'94 Karamo and her campaign did not respond to multiple requests for comment by CNN. Karamo, a devout conservative Christian who has served on the board of Michigan\'92s Right to Life organization and on the board of an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://kristinakaramo.com/about"}}{\fldrslt anti-abortion pregnancy crisis center }}affiliate in Detroit, reiterated that belief in another episode from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/uh-oh-its-episode-0/id1526611407?i=1000487252209"}}{\fldrslt July 2020}}, in which she said humans have sacrificed other humans, including their own children, for \'93thousands of years, just packaged differently.\'94 \'93[People] were sacrificing them to these deities, which were really demons,\'94 she said. Karamo went on to say in a later episode of her podcast reviewed by CNN\'92s KFile that demonic possession is real and can be transmitted through \'93intimate relationships.\'94 \'93If a person has demonic possession \'97 I know it\'92s gonna sound really crazy to me saying that for some people, thinking like what?!\'94 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/imago-dei/id1526611407?i=1000490037609"}}{\fldrslt Karamo said in September 2020}}. \'93But having intimate relationships with people who are demonically possessed or oppressed \'97 I strongly believe that a person opens themselves up to possession. Demonic possession is real.\'94 Karamo has repeatedly touted to her followers that left-leaning elites are trying to push their own values, including pro-abortion views, on America. In a video she posted on her website in 2018 that CNN\'92s KFile accessed and reviewed, Karamo suggested a conspiracy in which left-leaning political operatives who now have business relationships with Netflix \'96 including prominent philanthropist and Democratic donor George Soros, former national security adviser Susan Rice and former President Barack Obama \'97 were taking over the streaming service to push pro-abortion content. \'93Is abortion funny to you? I would argue that it is nothing funny about abortion whatsoever, but apparently Netflix found it quite all right to air episode of Michelle Wolf\'92s show or season,\'94 Karamo said, describing the comedian\'92s short-lived Netflix show that aired in 2018 in which Wolf addressed having an abortion. \'93Why is Netflix putting out a series like this?\'94 she said. \'93All these people with these interesting political motives, all teaming up to create content for you to consume.\'94 The political newcomer rose to prominence in Michigan politics after she claimed she had witnessed fraud as a poll challenger during the 2020 election and baselessly claimed widespread voter fraud occurred in the state, signing on to an unsuccessful lawsuit. Karamo\'92s promotion of election denial and other conspiracy theories earned her Trump\'92s endorsement last fall. If elected to Michigan\'92s top election post, she would oversee the 2024 presidential election in which Trump is weighing a run. Karamo\'92s embrace of conspiracy theories has also led to her association with QAnon, a conspiracy theory that posits that Trump was working to take down a shadow cabal of Democratic politicians and elites running a child sex-trafficking ring and that one day soon cabal members will face arrests, tribunals and mass executions. Last year she {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.newsweek.com/republicans-attending-qanon-convention-las-vegas-nevada-1641562"}}{\fldrslt spoke}} at a QAnon conference in Las Vegas featuring prominent Q influencers. She {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/KristinaKaramo/status/904550895047802880"}}{\fldrslt previously called }}for a \'93citizenship arrest\'94 of Soros and said he \'93needs to be in jail\'94 and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/KristinaKaramo/status/904067878621782016"}}{\fldrslt spread the Clinton Kill List conspiracy}}, a baseless conspiracy theory that alleges former President Bill Clinton and Secretary of State Hillary Clinton have had dozens of people assassinated. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnn.com/2021/11/16/politics/kristina-karamo-michigan-secretary-of-state-candidate/index.html"}}{\fldrslt CNN previously reported}} some of Karamo\'92s beliefs and rhetoric, including her attacks against premarital sex and the LGBTQ community, such as that it will lead to the \'93normalization\'94 of pedophilia; her anti-vaxxer comments; and her election denialism. Karamo frequently attacks those she disagrees with as being instruments of Satan or \'93demonic,\'94 including the Democratic Party and the LGBTQ community.\AppleTypeServices \
\
